File-naming:

Filenames should be caps free, unless the name of the thing it contains
contains a capital letter (Like jQuery). Multiple words in the filename are
delimeted with a dot.

Comments:
// Normal descriptive comments
// Are like this, and can span
// multiple lines.

/**
 * FunctionName(argumentNum1, argumentNum2)
 * 
 * Functions are described like this. Where
 * this gets replaced by the description of the
 * function itself.
 * 
 * @param	int		argumentNum1		-	Description
 * @param	string		argumentNum2		-	Description
 * @return	bool					-	Description
 */

/**
 * @var		int		howOldAmI		-	Description
 */

/**
 * ClassName
 *
 * Class Description is placed here
 * 
 * @function	private		FunctionName1		-	Description
 * @function	public		FunctionName2		-	Description
 * @variable	private		privateVariable		-	Description
 * @variable	public		publicVariable		-	Description
 */

Function/Class/Variables:
class ClassName{
	private function FunctionName(argumentNum1, argumentNum2){
		this.variableName = argumentNum1;
	}
}